from torch.utils.data import TensorDataset, DataLoader
import pickle

X = pickle.load(open('data/XT2.pickle','rb'))[:,:,:100] # Dynamic
y = pickle.load(open('data/Y2.pickle','rb'))

train_bound = int(0.6*(X.shape[0]))
val_bound = int(0.8*(X.shape[0]))

X_train = X[:train_bound]
X_val = X[train_bound:val_bound]
X_test = X[val_bound:]
y_train = y[:train_bound]
y_val = y[train_bound:val_bound]
y_test = y[val_bound:]

X_train_t = torch.Tensor(X_train)
X_val_t = torch.Tensor(X_val)
X_test_t = torch.Tensor(X_test)
y_train_t = torch.Tensor(y_train)
y_val_t = torch.Tensor(y_val)
y_test_t = torch.Tensor(y_test)

BATCH_SIZE = 8

train_loader = DataLoader(TensorDataset(X_train_t, y_train_t), batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True)
val_loader = DataLoader(TensorDataset(X_val_t, y_val_t), batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=False)
test_loader = DataLoader(TensorDataset(X_test_t, y_test_t), batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=False)

# Model
class IMVFullLSTM_T_WISE_V2(torch.jit.ScriptModule):
    # Static Data (n, s_input_dim) + Dynamic Data (n, t, input_dim)
    # s_input_dim: dimension of the static data
    # input_dim  : dimension of the dynamic data
    __constants__ = ["n_units", "input_dim"]
    def __init__(self, input_dim, output_dim, s_input_dim,n_units, init_std=0.02, variable_wise=True):
        super().__init__()
        self.U_j = nn.Parameter(torch.randn(input_dim, 1, n_units)*init_std)
        self.W_j = nn.Parameter(torch.randn(input_dim, n_units, n_units)*init_std)
        self.b_j = nn.Parameter(torch.randn(input_dim, n_units)*init_std)
        self.W_i = nn.Linear(input_dim*(n_units+1), input_dim*n_units)
        self.W_f = nn.Linear(input_dim*(n_units+1), input_dim*n_units)
        self.W_o = nn.Linear(input_dim*(n_units+1), input_dim*n_units)
        self.F_alpha_n = nn.Parameter(torch.randn(input_dim, n_units, 1)*init_std)
        self.F_alpha_n_b = nn.Parameter(torch.randn(input_dim, 1)*init_std)
        self.F_beta = nn.Linear(2*n_units, 1)
        self.Phi = nn.Linear(2*n_units, output_dim)
        self.n_units = n_units
        self.input_dim = input_dim
        self.v = 1 if variable_wise else 2
        
        # Static Network
        """
        self.sfc = nn.Sequential(
                    nn.Linear(s_input_dim, 2 * n_units), 
                    nn.BatchNorm1d(2 * n_units),
                    nn.ReLU())
        """     
        self.s_input_dim = s_input_dim
        self.sfcs = nn.ModuleList()
        for i in range(s_input_dim):
            self.sfcs.append(nn.Linear(1, 2 * n_units) )
            #self.sfcs.append( nn.Sequential(
            #            nn.Linear(1, 2 * n_units), 
            #            nn.BatchNorm1d(2 * n_units),
            #            nn.ReLU()))
        print(self.sfcs[0])
        
    @torch.jit.script_method
    def forward(self, x, sx):
        # x: batch of dynamic data (batch_size, t, input_dim)
        # sx: batch of static data (batch_size, s_input_dim)
        h_tilda_t = torch.zeros(x.shape[0], self.input_dim, self.n_units).cuda()
        c_t = torch.zeros(x.shape[0], self.input_dim*self.n_units).cuda()
        outputs = torch.jit.annotate(List[Tensor], [])
        
        s_params = torch.zeros(x.shape[0], self.s_input_dim, 2 * self.n_units).cuda()
        
        for t in range(x.shape[1]):
            # eq 1
            j_tilda_t = torch.tanh(torch.einsum("bij,ijk->bik", h_tilda_t, self.W_j) + \
                                   torch.einsum("bij,jik->bjk", x[:,t,:].unsqueeze(1), self.U_j) + self.b_j)
            inp =  torch.cat([x[:, t, :], h_tilda_t.view(h_tilda_t.shape[0], -1)], dim=1)
            # eq 2
            i_t = torch.sigmoid(self.W_i(inp))
            f_t = torch.sigmoid(self.W_f(inp))
            o_t = torch.sigmoid(self.W_o(inp))
            # eq 3
            c_t = c_t*f_t + i_t*j_tilda_t.reshape(j_tilda_t.shape[0], -1)
            # eq 4
            h_tilda_t = (o_t*torch.tanh(c_t)).view(h_tilda_t.shape[0], self.input_dim, self.n_units)
            outputs += [h_tilda_t]
        outputs = torch.stack(outputs)
        outputs = outputs.permute(1, 0, 2, 3)
        # eq 8
        alphas = torch.tanh(torch.einsum("btij,ijk->btik", outputs, self.F_alpha_n) +self.F_alpha_n_b)
        alphas = torch.exp(alphas)
        alphas = (alphas/torch.sum(alphas, dim=self.v, keepdim=True))

        g_n = torch.sum(alphas*outputs, dim=1)
        
        # static cell
        for icol,sfc in enumerate(self.sfcs):
            s_params[:,icol,:] = sfc(sx[:,(icol):(icol+1)])
        #h_static = self.sfc(sx)
        
        hg = torch.cat([g_n, h_tilda_t], dim=2)
        # concat static + dynamic

        hg = torch.concat([hg, s_params], dim=1)
        mu = self.Phi(hg)
        betas = torch.tanh(self.F_beta(hg))
        betas = torch.exp(betas)
        betas = betas/torch.sum(betas, dim=1, keepdim=True)
        mean = torch.sigmoid(torch.sum(betas*mu, dim=1))
        return mean, alphas, betas

torch.cuda.empty_cache()
model = IMVFullLSTM_T_WISE_V2(X_train_t.shape[2], 1,s_input_dim, 16).cuda()
opt = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.005)
epoch_scheduler = torch.optim.lr_scheduler.StepLR(opt, 20, gamma=0.9)
from sklearn.metrics import f1_score, accuracy_score
    
epochs = 200
loss = nn.BCELoss()#MSELoss()
patience = 25
min_val_loss = 9999
counter = 0
for i in range(epochs):
    mse_train = 0
    for batch_x, batch_y in train_loader:
        batch_s = x_static[batch_x[:,0,0].to(torch.long)].cuda() # Batch DataのユーザーIDでStaticデータのBatchを作成
        batch_x = batch_x[:,1:].cuda()
        batch_y = batch_y.cuda()

        opt.zero_grad()
        y_pred, alphas, betas = model(batch_x, batch_s)
        y_pred = y_pred.squeeze(1)
        l = loss(y_pred, batch_y.squeeze())
        l.backward()
        mse_train += l.item()*batch_x.shape[0]
        opt.step()
    epoch_scheduler.step()
    with torch.no_grad():
        mse_val = 0
        preds = []
        true = []
        for batch_x, batch_y in val_loader:
            batch_s = x_static[batch_x[:,0,0].to(torch.long)].cuda()
            batch_x = batch_x[:,1:].cuda()
            batch_y = batch_y.cuda()
            
            output, alphas, betas = model(batch_x, batch_s)
            output = output.squeeze(1)
            preds.append(output.detach().cpu().numpy())
            true.append(batch_y.detach().cpu().numpy())
            mse_val += loss(output, batch_y.squeeze()).item()*batch_x.shape[0]
    preds = np.concatenate(preds)
    true = np.concatenate(true)
    
    if min_val_loss > mse_val:
        min_val_loss = mse_val
        print("Saving...")
        torch.save(model.state_dict(), "imv_full_lstm.pt")
        counter = 0
    else: 
        counter += 1
    
    if counter == patience:
        break
    print("Iter: ", i, "train: ", (mse_train/len(X_train_t)), "val: ", (mse_val/len(X_val_t)))
    if(i % 10 == 0):
        #preds = preds*(y_train_max - y_train_min) + y_train_min
        #true = true*(y_train_max - y_train_min) + y_train_min
        #mse = mean_squared_error(true, preds)
        #mae = mean_absolute_error(true, preds)
        f1 = f1_score(true, np.round(preds))
        acc = accuracy_score(true, np.round(preds))
        print("lr: ", opt.param_groups[0]["lr"])
        print("accuracy: ", acc, "f1: ",f1)
        #plt.figure(figsize=(20, 10))
        #plt.plot(preds)
        #plt.plot(true)
        #plt.show()
